HEADWORD: Lactim
<hw>Lac"tim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lactic</ets> +
<ets>im</ets>ido.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a series of
anhydrides resembling the lactams, but of an imido type; <as>as, isatine
is a <ex>lactim</ex></as>. Cf. <er>Lactam</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lactimide</ent>⟦br⟧
